oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The Moser Family
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: [front] Daniel Miller Moser, Elizabeth Jane Brakebill Moser, Mary Ann Blankenship; [rear] William Ira, Jim Barb, Rebecca (Becca) Pardue, Barbara Bible, Frances (Frankie) Moser, Joe Seiss, John Morgan, Ben Harris.

Taken at Old Tate Simpson home in Vonore. The home belonged to John Tate Simpson (1856-1927) and his son Joe Tate Simpson (1905-1976). Both are buried in Sweetwater, Tennessee and were lifelong East Tennessee residents. Daniel Miller Moser (1839-1905) was the son of Francis Moser (1812-1865) and Elizabeth Moser. Daniel's wife was Elizabeth Jane Brakebill Moser (1839-1907). Rebecca Moser Pardue (1869-1927), William Ira Pardue (1904-1974), James P Barb (1859-1933).
